description: This table stores medications received from outside sources.

columns.name: DOCUMENT_ID
columns.description: This item stores the Received Document record ID.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE_REAL
columns.description: This is a numeric representation of the date of this encounter in your system. The integer portion of the number specifies the date of the encounter. The digits after the decimal point indicate multiple visits on one day.

columns.name: LINE
columns.description: The line number for the information associated with this contact. Multiple pieces of information can be associated with this contact.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE
columns.description: The date of this contact in calendar format.

columns.name: MED_REF_ID
columns.description: This item stores the unique reference ID.

columns.name: MED_NAME
columns.description: This item stores the medication name.

columns.name: MED_ID
columns.description: This item stores the mapped Medication ID for the medication.

columns.name: MED_DIRECTIONS
columns.description: This item stores free text sig for the medication.

columns.name: MED_DOSE
columns.description: This item stores dosage for the medication.

columns.name: MED_DISCRETE_DOSE
columns.description: This item stores discrete dose for the medication.

columns.name: MED_ROUTE
columns.description: This item stores route information for the medication.

columns.name: MED_ROUTE_ID_C_NAME
columns.description:
This item stores mapped route information for the medication.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes

columns.name: MED_QUANTITY
columns.description: This item stores the medication quantity.

columns.name: MED_IS_LONG_TERM_YN
columns.description:
This item is set if the medication is long term.


May contain organization-specific values: No


 Category Entries: 


No


Yes

columns.name: MED_START_DATE
columns.description: This item stores the start date of the medication.

columns.name: MED_END_DATE
columns.description: This item stores the end date of the medication.

columns.name: MED_FORM
columns.description: This item stores the form of the medication.

columns.name: MED_FORM_ID_C_NAME
columns.description:
This item stores the mapped form of the medication.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes

columns.name: MED_DOSE_UNIT
columns.description: This item stores the dose units associated with the medication.

columns.name: MED_FREQ
columns.description: This item stores the frequency to take this medication.

columns.name: MED_FREQ_ID
columns.description: This item stores the mapped frequency to take this medication.

columns.name: MED_FREQ_ID_FREQ_NAME
columns.description: The name of the frequency record.

columns.name: MED_ORIG_REFILLS
columns.description: This item stores the original refills for the medications.

columns.name: MED_REFILL_REMAIN
columns.description: This item stores the remaining refills for the medications.

columns.name: MED_RSN_FOR_DISC
columns.description: This item stores the reason for discontinuation.

columns.name: MED_RSN_FOR_DISC_C_NAME
columns.description:
This item stores the mapped reason for discontinuation.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes

columns.name: MED_SRC_ORD_ID
columns.description: This item stores the record ID of the source medication record.

columns.name: MED_TYPE_OF_CHNG_C_NAME
columns.description:
This item stores the type of change associated with the medication.


May contain organization-specific values: No


 Category Entries: 


Receive


Edit


Delete

columns.name: MED_SRC_DXR_CSN
columns.description: This item will store the contact serial number (CSN) of the Received Document record that owns the instance of this medication.

columns.name: MED_DUP_GRP_ID
columns.description: This item will store a duplicate grouping identifier.

columns.name: MED_DUP_OVRD_ORD_ID
columns.description: This item stores the record identifier of the local medication that this external medication should be grouped with.

columns.name: MED_STATUS_C_NAME
columns.description:
This item stores the status of the medications.  


May contain organization-specific values: No


 Category Entries: 


Active


No Longer Active


On Hold


Prior History


Pre-Starting Action

columns.name: MED_REQ_RES_COMMENT
columns.description: The response comments received with an incoming electronic prescription message.

columns.name: MED_PRIM_DX_ID
columns.description: The primary diagnosis for the medication specified within the incoming electronic prescription

columns.name: MED_SEC_DX_ID
columns.description: The secondary diagnosis for the medication specified within the incoming electronic prescription.

columns.name: MED_LAST_UPD_DTTM
columns.description: This item stores the date and time when the medication was last updated by the external system.

columns.name: MED_PT_SRC_APP_C_NAME
columns.description:
If this medication is a patient-entered medication (i.e. Received Documents type = 25), this item stores the application which was used to edit the medication for the contact (e.g. MyChart or Welcome). If blank, this is assumed to be MyChart.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


MyChart


Welcome

columns.name: MED_EARLIESTFILL_DT
columns.description: The first or earliest date on which the medication in the medication prescribed segment of the external e-prescription can be filled.

columns.name: MED_IS_MIXTURE_YN
columns.description:
This column indicates whether the medication in the medication prescribed segment of the external e-prescription, received through the incoming e-prescribing interface, is a mixture.


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: MED_IS_LONG_TERM_YN

columns.name: MED_IS_SUPPLY_YN
columns.description:
This column indicates whether the medication in the medication prescribed segment of the external e-prescription, received through the incoming e-prescribing interface, is a medication supply (for example, a test strip).


 The category values for this column were already listed for column: MED_IS_LONG_TERM_YN

columns.name: MED_DEA_CODE_C_NAME
columns.description:
The DEA schedule for the medication in the medication prescribed segment of the external e-prescription received through the incoming e-prescribing interface. 


May contain organization-specific values: Yes


 Category Entries: 


Non-Scheduled Medication


C-I No Accepted Medical Use


C-II High Abuse Potential


C-III Moderate Dependence


C-IV Limited Dependence


C-V Limited Abuse Potential


Undeterminable


C-VI State Scheduled


C-VII State Scheduled


C-VIII State Scheduled


C-IX State Scheduled


C-X State Scheduled
